Generate Java code that creates an abstract base type without boilerplate using Java’s built-in abstract classes and abstract methods, like this:

```java
abstract class MyClass {
    public abstract void myMethod();
}
```

This will create an abstract class `MyClass` that has an abstract method `myMethod`, which can be implemented by any subclass of `MyClass`. The Java `abstract` keyword enforces the abstract contract, and Java’s default constructor behavior means you don’t need to explicitly write a constructor (`__init__`-equivalent) unless you have custom initialization logic.
